      "rationale": "Predicted relative hemolysis index compared against bench measurements at all 5 operating points. Mean absolute error of 18.3% observed, which exceeds the ±15% acceptance band established for Gradation 2. Experimental uncertainty was characterised (±5% on RH measurement) but the simulation-to-experiment discrepancy at two high-shear operating points falls outside the combined uncertainty interval. The team noted the trend agreement is satisfactory and attributed deviations to minor geometric tolerances in the test article. Output comparison is assessed at Gradation 1 only."
